  "content": "ID: T1591\nTitle: Gather Victim Org Information\nURL: https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1591\nAdversaries may gather information about the victim's organization that can be used during targeting. Information about an organization may include a variety of details, including the names of divisions/departments, specifics of business operations, as well as the roles and responsibilities of key employees. Adversaries may gather this information in various ways, such as direct elicitation via Phishing for Information . Information about an organization may also be exposed to adversaries via online or other accessible data sets (ex: Social Media or Search Victim-Owned Websites ). [1] [2] Gathering this information may reveal opportunities for other forms of reconnaissance (ex: Phishing for Information or Search Open Websites/Domains ), establishing operational resources (ex: Establish Accounts or Compromise Accounts ), and/or initial access (ex: Phishing or Trusted Relationship ).",
  "category": "Article",
  "source": "Local Storage",
